title: Week 6: Top Box Scores
text: Week 6: Top Box Scores Ben Mitchum Talk about it in the kansasgridiron Message Boards Week 6 in the Sunflower State saw four different quarterbacks eclipse the 300 passing yards mark. One passer connected on seven touchdown passes, matched only by a PlayStation-esque effort from a running back in the 8-Man classification. KansasGridiron runs down some of the week's best in the latest edition of Top Box Scores. Passing Levi Archer of Class 4A-II Goodland was 29 of 43, throwing for 397 yards and five touchdowns. The Cowboys beat 3A Russell 46-41.3A Pittsburg-Colgan quarterback Ryan Cedeno completed 17 of 24 passes for 370 yards and three TDs. He also rushed for a score in a 43-40 loss to 4A-II Columbus. 6A Dodge City QB Caden Walters connected on 14 of 24 attempts for 342 yards and three TDs in a 37-3 victory over 4A-I Hays.Nick Spencer of 8-Man II Southern Coffey County was 19 of 33 for 329 yards and seven scores in a 68-32 victory over 8-Man II Chetopa. Rushing 8-Man II Pike Valley running back Lane Peters rushed for a staggering 428 yards on 35 carries, crossing the goalline seven times in a 74-50 victory over 8-Man II Frankfort. RB Cole Sramek carried 32 times for 280 yards and 3 TDs as 8-Man I Atwood-Rawlins downed Stockton 68-40.Kody Gonzalez of 5A Goddard gained 261 yards on 22 carries and a score as Goddard defeated 5A Andover 33-31. 4A-II Columbus RB Jace McDown ran for 255 yards and four TDs in a 43-40 victory over 3A CNC league rival Pittsburg-Colgan. Receiving 6A Dodge City receiver Eric Reid caught five passes for 208 yards and three TDs in a 37-3 win over 4A-I Hays. His first three receptions went for touchdowns of 71, 61, and 52 yards.4A-II Goodland saw receiver Darian Kent catch seven balls for 191 yards and a pair of scores in a 46-41 victory over 3A Russell.Sawyer Esch of 3A Pittsburg-Colgan had five catches for 187 yards and a TD in a 43-40 loss to 4A-II Columbus.Once again, 4A-I Andover Central dual-sport star Darraja Parnell came up big with six catches for 179 yards and three TDs in a 44-33 victory over 6A Haysville-Campus. Top Defensive Performances Linebacker Chase Crawford of 5A Valley Center continues to put up big defensive numbers. He registered 22 tackles in a 25-19 loss to 5A Goddard-Eisenhower. In 8-Man II action, South Barber LB Spencer Kimmell had 21 tackles with two tackles for loss in a 54-18 victory over Norwich. Cooper Griffith of 3A Scott City had a good all-around game against 4A-I power Ulysses in a 35-0 statement win. He logged 16 tackles and two TFLs to go with his 178 yards rushing and 2 TDs. Griffith led a defensive effort that held Ulysses star Ian Rudzik to just 29 yards on 15 carries, well below his 246 yards per game average. Kansas NEWS
